1
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:34,980
=Wonder Wall=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,910
=Episode 19=

3
00:01:42,439 --> 00:01:42,959
Dad,

4
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:44,159
how did you get here?

5
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:46,560
The surgery isn't over?

6
00:01:47,159 --> 00:01:47,920
What did the doctor say?

7
00:01:48,159 --> 00:01:49,840
The doctor said it wasn't serious.

8
00:01:50,159 --> 00:01:51,239
Your mom is such a nice person.

9
00:01:51,599 --> 00:01:52,439
She'll be fine.

10
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:54,680
Yu Ming just called me.

11
00:01:54,719 --> 00:01:55,319
Wenwen's been found.

12
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:56,000
Yes.

13
00:01:56,040 --> 00:01:56,920
Wenwen's mostly fine.

14
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:57,680
Just a twisted ankle.

15
00:01:57,840 --> 00:01:59,040
And there are some minor scrapes.

16
00:01:59,159 --> 00:02:00,239
Kids heal fast.

17
00:02:00,319 --> 00:02:01,200
Don't worry.

18
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,200
So many of us

19
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:02,959
are here.

20
00:02:03,159 --> 00:02:04,040
Lanying needs you.

21
00:02:04,079 --> 00:02:05,079
Don't keep running back here.

22
00:02:08,599 --> 00:02:09,039
Hello.

23
00:02:09,639 --> 00:02:10,479
Is this Sun Lanying's family?

24
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:11,560
Yes.

25
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:12,759
Her blood pressure

26
00:02:12,759 --> 00:02:13,639
suddenly spiked.

27
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:15,039
She's had projectile vomiting.

28
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:16,159
Please come quickly.

29
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:17,360
What happened?

30
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:24,240
Doctor, how is she?

31
00:02:24,319 --> 00:02:25,759
She has a minor fracture in her calf

32
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,240
and some minor scrapes.

33
00:02:27,479 --> 00:02:28,159
All taken care of.

34
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:28,759
Thank you.

35
00:02:28,879 --> 00:02:29,360
Does it hurt?

36
00:02:29,439 --> 00:02:30,039
No.

37
00:02:30,159 --> 00:02:31,000
It'll heal.

38
00:02:33,159 --> 00:02:34,479
Maybe you should go see Du Lei.

39
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:35,120
Yes.

40
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:35,520
Okay.

41
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:35,960
Keep in touch.

42
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:36,520
We'll take her mom.

43
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:37,080
Alright.

44
00:02:37,159 --> 00:02:37,879
Be careful.

45
00:02:37,879 --> 00:02:38,400
Okay.

46
00:02:41,908 --> 00:02:44,194
(In Operation)

47
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:53,240
Mom.

48
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:54,560
Wenwen.

49
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:55,680
She's fine.

50
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:56,680
Just a minor fracture in her calf

51
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:57,840
and some minor scrapes.

52
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:58,199
Is

53
00:02:58,240 --> 00:02:59,319
your mom not out yet?

54
00:02:59,439 --> 00:03:00,039
No.

55
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:01,199
The doctor said it wasn't serious.

56
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:02,159
Your dad came just now.

57
00:03:02,159 --> 00:03:02,879
He received a call.

58
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:04,199
Your mom might not be well.

59
00:03:04,199 --> 00:03:04,800
You should go.

60
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:05,319
Give it to me.

61
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:07,000
What happened to her?

62
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:09,120
I couldn't hear. Just go!

63
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:09,599
Alright.

64
00:03:10,639 --> 00:03:11,080
Wenwen,

65
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:12,639
are you hungry? Want something to eat?

66
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:13,360
Fried chicken.

67
00:03:13,759 --> 00:03:14,560
You want fried chicken?

68
00:03:15,199 --> 00:03:16,039
I'll go buy you some.

69
00:03:16,319 --> 00:03:17,159
I'll go get her some.

70
00:03:17,159 --> 00:03:17,520
Okay.

71
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:28,639
Let me see your face.

72
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:31,120
Any other injuries?

73
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:32,159
No.

74
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:33,199
Don't put your hand here.

75
00:03:34,159 --> 00:03:34,919
These are bandaged?

76
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:36,960
It's fine.

77
00:03:37,479 --> 00:03:38,080
Does it hurt?

78
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:39,639
No.

79
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:42,840
Good, you're pretty tough.

80
00:03:45,719 --> 00:03:47,199
I was just saving my dad's face.

81
00:03:47,879 --> 00:03:48,719
Didn't you say

82
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:50,120
if I live, he lives?

83
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:51,800
If I'm strong, he's strong?

84
00:03:52,039 --> 00:03:52,680
I did say that.

85
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,240
You have good memory.

86
00:03:59,080 --> 00:03:59,599
Mom,

87
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:02,120
you don't blame me?

88
00:04:02,599 --> 00:04:03,280
Blame you for what?

89
00:04:03,439 --> 00:04:05,159
Grandma got hurt saving me.

90
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:11,879
These days,

91
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:13,800
I've been blaming myself.

92
00:04:14,759 --> 00:04:16,240
But you and Grandma both came back safe.

93
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:17,879
I don't blame anyone anymore.

94
00:04:19,319 --> 00:04:20,560
It's over. It's okay.

95
00:04:22,399 --> 00:04:22,959
It's okay.

96
00:04:24,279 --> 00:04:25,279
You wanted to spend

97
00:04:25,319 --> 00:04:26,759
over 1,000 to get your grandma a perm.

98
00:04:27,560 --> 00:04:28,680
Get one for me too.

99
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,360
I also need it.

100
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:32,839
Mom,

101
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:34,879
I'm a minor,

102
00:04:34,959 --> 00:04:36,000
and I'm already in debt

103
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:37,759
to Grandma for 1,000.

104
00:04:38,519 --> 00:04:39,720
What happened

105
00:04:39,839 --> 00:04:41,079
to your usual

106
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:42,000
upright image?

107
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:43,639
Why are you so small-minded?

108
00:04:44,439 --> 00:04:44,959
That's fair.

109
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:46,759
Give your dad a perm instead.

110
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:51,560
Yu Wenwen,

111
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:54,000
I can't lose you.

112
00:04:55,399 --> 00:04:56,439
Don't forget me.

113
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:58,639
Mom.

114
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:02,199
Stop crying.

115
00:05:04,623 --> 00:05:06,037
(In Operation)

116
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:23,517
(Resuscitation Room)

117
00:05:25,639 --> 00:05:26,040
Doctor,

118
00:05:26,079 --> 00:05:26,920
how is she doing?

119
00:05:27,199 --> 00:05:28,560
She's out of danger.

120
00:05:29,079 --> 00:05:30,160
But this time,

121
00:05:30,199 --> 00:05:32,199
she's had a hemorrhagic stroke.

122
00:05:32,439 --> 00:05:33,639
The hematoma is causing

123
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:34,879
a mass effect.

124
00:05:34,959 --> 00:05:35,879
The pressure is compressing

125
00:05:36,160 --> 00:05:37,079
her brain tissue.

126
00:05:37,279 --> 00:05:38,160
So the damage

127
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:38,920
has already occurred.

128
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:40,399
Once the nervous system

129
00:05:40,519 --> 00:05:41,480
is damaged,

130
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:43,240
recovery is very slow

131
00:05:43,519 --> 00:05:44,680
and unpredictable.

132
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:46,120
As her family,

133
00:05:46,160 --> 00:05:47,439
you need to

134
00:05:47,759 --> 00:05:48,519
follow the treatment,

135
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:49,839
and prepare for a long road ahead.

136
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:51,560
You should have confidence

137
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:52,480
as well as patience.

138
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:53,920
And please, don't do anything

139
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:54,879
to upset her emotionally.

140
00:05:55,079 --> 00:05:55,560
I understand.

141
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:56,240
Thank you.

142
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:56,639
No problem.

143
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:02,639
Something happened to Mr. Yu's family.

144
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:03,759
We should go see them.

145
00:06:03,839 --> 00:06:04,680
Go see Mr. Yu.

146
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,120
This is the fish I dried.

147
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:09,720
At least, send something over.

148
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,800
Mr. Yu's been through
something terrible.

149
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:13,079
This is a copper coin sword

150
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,360
passed down in our family.

151
00:06:14,519 --> 00:06:15,680
Take it to Mr. Yu.

152
00:06:15,839 --> 00:06:16,519
It'll protect him.

153
00:06:16,519 --> 00:06:16,839
Okay.

154
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:18,040
Alright, we're going now.

155
00:06:18,079 --> 00:06:18,560
Let's go.

156
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:19,920
Don't bring that. Let's go.

157
00:06:19,959 --> 00:06:20,759
We're leaving.

158
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:22,519
We're leaving. Go.

159
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:23,959
Okay.

160
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:25,879
Send our regards to Mr. Yu.

161
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:27,600
We're leaving.

162
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,480
Drive safe.

163
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:48,399
Dad,

164
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:49,519
maybe you should go

165
00:06:49,519 --> 00:06:50,040
check on Mom.

166
00:06:50,759 --> 00:06:52,360
Grandpa and I will manage here.

167
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:56,360
Good girl, you're so sweet.

168
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:57,639
You're worried about her, right?

169
00:06:58,879 --> 00:06:59,519
Alright then.

170
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:00,879
Dad,

171
00:07:01,319 --> 00:07:02,759
I'll go check on Yitong.

172
00:07:02,839 --> 00:07:04,279
If everything is fine, I'll come back.

173
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:05,720
You should get some sleep.

174
00:07:05,839 --> 00:07:06,720
Why do you just sit there?

175
00:07:06,759 --> 00:07:07,759
There are two beds here.

176
00:07:07,879 --> 00:07:08,680
Just lie down

177
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:10,040
and get some sleep, okay?

178
00:07:11,519 --> 00:07:12,839
When Grandma wakes up,

179
00:07:12,879 --> 00:07:14,399
don't let her get too worked up.

180
00:07:14,759 --> 00:07:16,079
It's bad for her.

181
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:17,639
I'm leaving.

182
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:37,360
She fell asleep.

183
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:39,319
How is your mom?

184
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:40,920
She's out of danger.

185
00:07:41,079 --> 00:07:41,720
She's fine,

186
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:42,480
but

187
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:43,959
she might not speak

188
00:07:43,959 --> 00:07:44,720
for a while.

189
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,279
Can't speak?

190
00:07:52,439 --> 00:07:52,879
Alright.

191
00:07:52,879 --> 00:07:53,839
So she can't talk

192
00:07:53,839 --> 00:07:54,600
for now.

193
00:07:55,759 --> 00:07:57,360
She's got a really sharp tongue,

194
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:58,600
cuts everyone in sight.

195
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:01,279
But honestly, when she cuts others,

196
00:08:01,279 --> 00:08:02,120
she's also

197
00:08:02,759 --> 00:08:04,160
hurting herself. Getting angry.

198
00:08:04,839 --> 00:08:05,560
So be it.

199
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:07,360
Just let it be.

200
00:08:08,040 --> 00:08:08,759
Perhaps this way,

201
00:08:08,759 --> 00:08:10,240
she'd be in a good mood
without getting upset,

202
00:08:10,399 --> 00:08:11,720
maybe she'll live even longer.

203
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:15,000
Maybe this is a good time

204
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:16,759
to see if your dad

205
00:08:16,759 --> 00:08:17,480
can move back.

206
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:18,439
The two are

207
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:19,600
companions in old age.

208
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:20,759
At a time like this...

209
00:08:22,360 --> 00:08:22,800
Right?

210
00:08:26,199 --> 00:08:27,800
Did Guo Li say anything to you?

211
00:08:30,439 --> 00:08:30,959
No.

212
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:01,519
Doctor,

213
00:09:01,919 --> 00:09:02,919
how is Du Lei doing now?

214
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:03,919
His life is still in danger.

215
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:04,519
Then...

216
00:09:17,639 --> 00:09:18,679
Have some water, Mom.

217
00:09:21,559 --> 00:09:22,399
Here.

218
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,080
Okay, take it slow.

219
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:39,200
Mom,

220
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:41,840
I never really listened to

221
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:43,919
all your nagging before.

222
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:46,919
Now I remember it all.

223
00:09:47,554 --> 00:09:49,394
♪You said, don't rush♪

224
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:52,039
You said if I kept everything to myself,

225
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:54,240
I'd get ill.

226
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:55,314
♪That cup of tea on the table♪

227
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:58,759
You said I always rush into things.

228
00:09:58,861 --> 00:10:00,200
♪Nothing much has happened♪

229
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:01,080
I'll get hurt.

230
00:10:02,034 --> 00:10:03,919
♪Nothing earth-shattering at all♪

231
00:10:03,919 --> 00:10:06,360
So why is it you who fell?

232
00:10:07,639 --> 00:10:08,960
You said you can't always

233
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:10,559
be there to catch me.

234
00:10:11,759 --> 00:10:13,679
But just knowing you're behind me,

235
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:16,399
when I charge forward,

236
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:18,559
that's enough to keep me going.

237
00:10:18,559 --> 00:10:20,314
♪If the umbrella's downstairs♪

238
00:10:20,314 --> 00:10:21,634
♪We'll just get♪

239
00:10:21,634 --> 00:10:22,914
♪A little wet♪

240
00:10:23,648 --> 00:10:26,874
♪Let's wait for the rain to stop♪

241
00:10:26,874 --> 00:10:29,714
♪Instead of worrying so much♪

242
00:10:29,714 --> 00:10:32,074
♪Maybe this time♪

243
00:10:32,074 --> 00:10:35,279
♪I'll learn to let go♪

244
00:10:35,279 --> 00:10:35,799
Ming,

245
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:40,080
how is your mom?

246
00:10:40,679 --> 00:10:41,360
She's okay.

247
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:42,879
Did Du Lei wake up?

248
00:10:43,559 --> 00:10:44,279
I asked the nurse.

249
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:45,320
He hasn't woken up yet.

250
00:10:46,159 --> 00:10:46,639
I don't know

251
00:10:46,639 --> 00:10:48,000
where Chen Zinuo's mom went.

252
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:49,519
It was my fault.

253
00:10:49,519 --> 00:10:50,360
I shouldn't have let Zinuo

254
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:51,519
go find her mom alone.

255
00:10:56,559 --> 00:10:57,080
It's okay.

256
00:10:57,080 --> 00:10:58,480
The police are involved now.

257
00:10:58,519 --> 00:10:59,759
Don't worry.

258
00:10:59,759 --> 00:11:00,360
She'll be fine.

259
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:04,480
Did our forensics team

260
00:11:04,679 --> 00:11:05,799
compare

261
00:11:05,919 --> 00:11:06,519
these two photos?

262
00:11:06,519 --> 00:11:07,080
Yes.

263
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,320
It's very likely

264
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:09,279
they're the same person.

265
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:11,200
I also suspect

266
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:12,720
he's the owner of Bridgeway Financial,

267
00:11:12,759 --> 00:11:13,200
Du Lei.

268
00:11:13,919 --> 00:11:14,480
Du Lei?

269
00:11:16,879 --> 00:11:17,279
Li Jin,

270
00:11:17,639 --> 00:11:18,440
Chen Zinuo's mother.

271
00:11:18,679 --> 00:11:20,279
She appeared

272
00:11:20,279 --> 00:11:21,559
at suspicious times

273
00:11:21,559 --> 00:11:22,240
and locations

274
00:11:22,279 --> 00:11:22,919
in these two cases.

275
00:11:23,399 --> 00:11:24,559
And both victims

276
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:25,519
had frequent contact

277
00:11:25,519 --> 00:11:26,360
with Li Jin.

278
00:11:26,559 --> 00:11:27,559
This is no coincidence.

279
00:11:28,679 --> 00:11:29,679
Li Jin

280
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:30,879
must have been involved

281
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:32,200
in these two cases.

282
00:12:10,039 --> 00:12:10,720
You're awake.

283
00:12:12,279 --> 00:12:12,840
Grandma.

284
00:12:13,519 --> 00:12:14,000
Mom.

285
00:12:15,159 --> 00:12:16,200
Look, I'm back.

286
00:12:16,399 --> 00:12:17,279
I'm in great shape.

287
00:12:17,279 --> 00:12:18,120
I'm perfectly fine.

288
00:12:18,720 --> 00:12:20,000
Wenwen...

289
00:12:23,799 --> 00:12:24,399
Grandma,

290
00:12:24,799 --> 00:12:26,360
don't worry about me.

291
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:27,919
Grandma Fan was rescued too.

292
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:29,799
She broke a rib saving me,

293
00:12:30,039 --> 00:12:31,559
but the doctor said

294
00:12:31,759 --> 00:12:33,320
she'll be fine in a couple of days.

295
00:12:34,159 --> 00:12:35,360
You also need to follow

296
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:36,279
the doctor's orders too.

297
00:12:36,399 --> 00:12:37,840
Then you'll recover soon.

298
00:12:40,279 --> 00:12:41,759
Don't be sad.

299
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:43,639
I was wrong, mom.

300
00:12:43,919 --> 00:12:44,960
Don't yell at me anymore.

301
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:45,600
Don't get worked up.

302
00:12:45,639 --> 00:12:46,759
You can't get upset right now.

303
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:51,759
Clothes?

304
00:12:52,519 --> 00:12:53,159
My clothes?

305
00:12:53,879 --> 00:12:54,320
They stink?

306
00:12:56,759 --> 00:12:57,519
Your clothes?

307
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,799
You need a change of clothes?

308
00:13:01,159 --> 00:13:02,519
You want me to go home

309
00:13:02,519 --> 00:13:03,200
and get them?

310
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:05,720
But you need to wear
the hospital gown here.

311
00:13:05,759 --> 00:13:06,759
Bringing your own won't help.

312
00:13:08,159 --> 00:13:08,720
Ming.

313
00:13:08,799 --> 00:13:09,480
Don't be anxious.

314
00:13:09,519 --> 00:13:10,039
Ming,

315
00:13:11,679 --> 00:13:12,639
your mom misses home.

316
00:13:12,919 --> 00:13:13,799
She wants to go home soon.

317
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:16,519
Okay.

318
00:13:16,879 --> 00:13:18,919
I'll go get your clothes ready.

319
00:13:19,399 --> 00:13:19,720
Okay.

320
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:20,840
I'll go back to get them for you.

321
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:22,320
Dad, you...

322
00:13:22,399 --> 00:13:23,159
You watch over mom.

323
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:23,600
Okay.

324
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:24,399
Be good, Wenwen.

325
00:13:24,519 --> 00:13:25,480
I'll be back soon.

326
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:26,360
Okay.

327
00:13:37,919 --> 00:13:38,480
Don't worry.

328
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:39,720
Don't get upset.

329
00:13:39,879 --> 00:13:40,720
Stay calm.

330
00:14:02,830 --> 00:14:06,065
(New Character Workbook,
Class 7, Grade 4, Yu Feng)

331
00:14:41,980 --> 00:14:44,404
(Demo for Mr. Money,
Recorded on 2011.7.21, Yu Ming)

332
00:15:00,720 --> 00:15:01,120
Mom.

333
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:02,559
Mom,

334
00:15:03,240 --> 00:15:04,799
I finished my new song.

335
00:15:05,159 --> 00:15:06,120
Do you want to hear it?

336
00:15:07,919 --> 00:15:09,120
You recorded it with your own money.

337
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:10,039
What's so impressive about it?

338
00:15:10,559 --> 00:15:11,960
Everything your brother earns,

339
00:15:12,080 --> 00:15:13,440
goes straight to you.

340
00:15:14,240 --> 00:15:15,000
Good-for-nothing.

341
00:15:15,314 --> 00:15:17,480
♪Where have you gone?♪

342
00:15:17,514 --> 00:15:19,320
(Demo for Mr. Money,
Recorded on 2011.7.21, Yu Ming)

343
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:21,320
It's really good.

344
00:15:21,320 --> 00:15:21,720
Really?

345
00:15:23,159 --> 00:15:23,759
Let me tell you,

346
00:15:24,399 --> 00:15:25,639
this is the best song

347
00:15:25,679 --> 00:15:27,159
you've ever made.

348
00:15:27,759 --> 00:15:29,000
It'll be a hit if you issue an album.

349
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:30,985
♪To those who pass me by♪

350
00:15:32,465 --> 00:15:35,280
♪You don't have to look at me♪

351
00:15:36,732 --> 00:15:40,046
♪Just keep walking your own way♪

352
00:15:41,011 --> 00:15:43,280
♪I'll manage on my own♪

353
00:15:46,907 --> 00:15:50,320
♪Is the rain falling hard♪

354
00:15:51,879 --> 00:15:52,559
Turns out

355
00:15:53,320 --> 00:15:54,480
you kept the song I wrote

356
00:15:55,639 --> 00:15:58,159
right next to you.

357
00:15:59,399 --> 00:15:59,919
Mom,

358
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:01,720
I thought

359
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:04,799
all you ever had for me
was disappointment.

360
00:16:05,519 --> 00:16:06,799
Now I finally understand

361
00:16:07,519 --> 00:16:08,960
the love and pain

362
00:16:09,559 --> 00:16:12,240
you hid inside.

363
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:14,840
Sorry, Mom.

364
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:18,720
I realized too late.

365
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:21,519
Am I not your own son?

366
00:16:21,519 --> 00:16:22,759
Did you pick me up somewhere?

367
00:16:23,159 --> 00:16:24,799
I've been trying very hard.

368
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:26,919
I had no choice, mom.

369
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:28,840
I want to be as excellent

370
00:16:28,840 --> 00:16:29,879
as my brother.

371
00:16:30,159 --> 00:16:31,559
But fate and you

372
00:16:31,799 --> 00:16:33,360
just can't see me.

373
00:16:33,639 --> 00:16:34,840
What can I do?

374
00:16:38,808 --> 00:16:42,043
♪The road ahead is still so long♪

375
00:16:43,121 --> 00:16:45,545
♪Where have you gone♪

376
00:16:47,306 --> 00:16:49,891
♪Under the blazing sun♪

377
00:16:51,645 --> 00:16:53,811
♪I keep heading north♪

378
00:16:55,970 --> 00:16:58,966
♪To those who pass me by♪

379
00:17:00,559 --> 00:17:01,159
Bigfoot,

380
00:17:01,480 --> 00:17:02,799
I'm feeding the chicken,

381
00:17:02,840 --> 00:17:03,159
packing up

382
00:17:03,159 --> 00:17:04,519
my parents' clothes

383
00:17:04,519 --> 00:17:06,400
Take them to the hospital.

384
00:17:06,559 --> 00:17:08,559
Then drop Wenwen off at school.

385
00:17:08,759 --> 00:17:10,440
After that, I'll go find you.

386
00:17:10,440 --> 00:17:11,359
Are you...

387
00:17:11,519 --> 00:17:12,319
Are you at the station?

388
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:13,319
I'm outside now.

389
00:17:13,319 --> 00:17:14,319
I can't get back for a while.

390
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:16,039
Okay then.

391
00:17:16,039 --> 00:17:17,400
I'll go back to Ziyu Garden.

392
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:18,400
I need to change the password.

393
00:17:18,519 --> 00:17:18,920
You can just

394
00:17:19,079 --> 00:17:20,279
pick me up

395
00:17:20,319 --> 00:17:21,079
on your way.

396
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:22,000
Okay then.

397
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:22,960
Wait for me at Unit 505.

398
00:17:23,920 --> 00:17:24,400
I got to go.

399
00:17:24,440 --> 00:17:25,079
Another call.

400
00:17:26,960 --> 00:17:27,319
Captain Guo,

401
00:17:27,559 --> 00:17:29,079
today we found a hidden camera

402
00:17:29,079 --> 00:17:30,039
inside an air conditioning unit

403
00:17:30,039 --> 00:17:30,759
at Du Lei's office.

404
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:31,640
It's confirmed that Li Jin

405
00:17:31,680 --> 00:17:32,519
took Chen Zinuo.

406
00:17:32,759 --> 00:17:33,839
Quickly check all the cameras

407
00:17:33,839 --> 00:17:34,880
near Du Lei's company.

408
00:17:35,119 --> 00:17:36,279
Find Li Jin's location now.

409
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:16,559
Jiajia is picking you up tonight.

410
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:17,920
Your mom already told her.

411
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:18,680
In the next few days,

412
00:18:19,079 --> 00:18:19,920
you'll stay

413
00:18:19,920 --> 00:18:20,640
with her.

414
00:18:21,160 --> 00:18:22,400
And at her place,

415
00:18:22,920 --> 00:18:23,599
don't act spoiled

416
00:18:23,599 --> 00:18:24,519
like you do at home.

417
00:18:24,519 --> 00:18:26,000
Listen to Jiajia,

418
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:26,400
Okay?

419
00:18:26,759 --> 00:18:27,799
Don't worry so much.

420
00:18:27,839 --> 00:18:28,960
I'm quite happy staying at her place.

421
00:18:29,480 --> 00:18:30,000
It's big.

422
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:31,200
I can have enough space

423
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:32,160
to move around.

424
00:18:32,799 --> 00:18:34,160
Wenwen.

425
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:35,000
You got injured?

426
00:18:35,680 --> 00:18:36,480
How could I not be injured

427
00:18:36,559 --> 00:18:37,519
from a narrow escape?

428
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:40,000
Her foot's not good right now.

429
00:18:40,039 --> 00:18:41,480
Look out for her at school.

430
00:18:41,680 --> 00:18:42,000
Okay.

431
00:18:42,240 --> 00:18:43,160
No problem.

432
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:43,519
Thank you.

433
00:19:05,039 --> 00:19:06,200
When your little red car

434
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:08,079
fancies another good-looking car,

435
00:19:08,119 --> 00:19:09,400
suddenly she's got no self-control?

436
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:11,759
Your car is just too attractive.

437
00:19:11,799 --> 00:19:12,960
It keeps seducing mine.

438
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:15,759
Currently,

439
00:19:16,279 --> 00:19:17,960
I have no time to fix your car for you.

440
00:19:18,039 --> 00:19:19,200
What are you saying?

441
00:19:19,319 --> 00:19:20,519
What's our relationship?

442
00:19:21,039 --> 00:19:21,920
Use your insurance.

443
00:19:23,519 --> 00:19:24,480
Let me tell you.

444
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:25,920
I found this

445
00:19:26,039 --> 00:19:27,440
MBA swimming class.

446
00:19:27,880 --> 00:19:29,000
Whole family thing. Really fun.

447
00:19:29,039 --> 00:19:30,079
I'll sign your family up too.

448
00:19:30,240 --> 00:19:31,519
Then wait for me to go with you.

449
00:19:31,559 --> 00:19:32,079
Get some practice.

450
00:19:32,319 --> 00:19:33,279
You can teach me

451
00:19:33,279 --> 00:19:34,119
your freestyle,

452
00:19:34,279 --> 00:19:35,160
that awesome one.

453
00:19:35,599 --> 00:19:36,880
Won't your daughter's legs

454
00:19:36,920 --> 00:19:38,359
need some rehab training?

455
00:19:38,440 --> 00:19:39,200
She can do butterfly.

456
00:19:39,599 --> 00:19:40,480
But I don't think your wife

457
00:19:40,519 --> 00:19:41,279
should go in the water.

458
00:19:41,559 --> 00:19:42,720
She talks too much.

459
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:43,920
She'd swallow water.

460
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:44,599
Right?

461
00:20:05,440 --> 00:20:06,079
Which way is it?

462
00:20:08,759 --> 00:20:09,200
Missed it.

463
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:10,880
What's going on?

464
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:11,400
It froze.

465
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:12,279
My phone froze.

466
00:20:12,319 --> 00:20:13,279
You bought a used box truck,

467
00:20:13,279 --> 00:20:14,759
and you buy used phones too?

468
00:20:14,839 --> 00:20:15,440
Your phone's junk.

469
00:20:15,440 --> 00:20:17,079
Use the old clunker. Ask Great-Grandma.

470
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:17,920
Yeah.

471
00:20:20,079 --> 00:20:21,039
Don't touch my gear shift.

472
00:20:24,519 --> 00:20:25,440
200 meters ahead,

473
00:20:25,799 --> 00:20:26,319
turn right.

474
00:20:26,440 --> 00:20:27,200
There is a gas station.

475
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:28,720
Zhu, I need to pee.

476
00:20:54,519 --> 00:20:55,200
Take it easy.

477
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:56,559
I can't hold it.

478
00:20:56,839 --> 00:20:57,519
Get some water too.

479
00:21:30,799 --> 00:21:31,240
Chui,

480
00:21:31,480 --> 00:21:33,160
I could barely keep my eyes on the GPS.

481
00:21:33,680 --> 00:21:34,400
I was really sleepy.

482
00:21:35,279 --> 00:21:36,319
You can't fall asleep.

483
00:21:36,720 --> 00:21:37,759
There's still a long way to go.

484
00:21:37,839 --> 00:21:38,599
We need to keep moving.

485
00:21:38,880 --> 00:21:39,240
Okay.

486
00:21:40,559 --> 00:21:40,960
Chui,

487
00:21:41,519 --> 00:21:42,400
maybe you should drive.

488
00:21:43,039 --> 00:21:44,119
Zhu can't go on either.

489
00:21:44,359 --> 00:21:45,119
You slept all the way here.

490
00:21:45,519 --> 00:21:46,680
When was I sleeping?

491
00:21:47,119 --> 00:21:48,079
I'll drive.

492
00:21:48,160 --> 00:21:49,039
You hurry up.

493
00:21:49,519 --> 00:21:49,960
I...

494
00:21:50,079 --> 00:21:51,279
I'm done.

495
00:21:51,319 --> 00:21:52,440
I'm waiting for you.

496
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:53,599
You hurry up and leave.

497
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:55,279
How could I pee when you're watching me?

498
00:21:55,279 --> 00:21:56,720
Hurry up. Don't waste time.

499
00:21:56,799 --> 00:21:57,680
Dawdling there.

500
00:21:57,680 --> 00:21:59,079
You're so fussy.

501
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:13,880
Well, this one, this one,

502
00:22:15,039 --> 00:22:15,400
and this.

503
00:22:15,559 --> 00:22:16,119
Three orders.

504
00:22:16,640 --> 00:22:16,920
Sure.

505
00:22:17,119 --> 00:22:17,440
To go.

506
00:22:18,119 --> 00:22:19,039
Extra rice.

507
00:22:19,079 --> 00:22:19,400
Okay.

508
00:22:42,359 --> 00:22:42,799
Where is he?

509
00:23:12,839 --> 00:23:13,400
Sorry,

510
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:14,960
my daughter's allergic to mangoes.

511
00:23:15,039 --> 00:23:15,359
Switch it.

512
00:23:15,599 --> 00:23:15,920
Okay.

513
00:23:20,680 --> 00:23:21,200
How much?

514
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:23,000
Let me scan.

515
00:23:24,119 --> 00:23:24,640
Thank you.

516
00:23:31,759 --> 00:23:32,039
Take care.

517
00:23:35,160 --> 00:23:35,599
Zhu.

518
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:39,559
Let me drive.

519
00:23:39,599 --> 00:23:41,160
You look so sleepy.

520
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:42,519
Give me the key.

521
00:23:53,240 --> 00:23:53,640
Zhu,

522
00:23:54,599 --> 00:23:55,519
why does the truck

523
00:23:55,519 --> 00:23:56,440
feel different now?

524
00:23:56,960 --> 00:23:57,880
You're just sleepy.

525
00:23:58,400 --> 00:23:59,440
What's that scent?

526
00:23:59,759 --> 00:24:00,680
Stop talking.

527
00:24:01,359 --> 00:24:02,240
Just focus on driving.

528
00:24:03,759 --> 00:24:04,359
Keep the change.

529
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:21,920
Yu Ming,

530
00:24:22,240 --> 00:24:23,119
why did you ask me to come?

531
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:28,359
Just come in first.

532
00:24:35,240 --> 00:24:35,799
So,

533
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:37,759
the 30 million found in the wall

534
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:39,799
belonged
to property developer Hu Deshuai.

535
00:24:40,319 --> 00:24:41,400
As for the 30 million

536
00:24:41,640 --> 00:24:43,359
in the basement,

537
00:24:43,759 --> 00:24:47,079
it belonged to Chen Liyang,

538
00:24:47,279 --> 00:24:48,240
the previous owner.

539
00:24:48,839 --> 00:24:50,400
What about
the three construction workers?

540
00:24:50,440 --> 00:24:52,079
They dug up that 30 million.

541
00:24:52,640 --> 00:24:53,200
But

542
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:54,640
they're not greedy.

543
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:56,359
They only wanted

544
00:24:56,720 --> 00:24:57,640
two million

545
00:24:57,680 --> 00:24:58,799
that Hu Deshuai owed them.

546
00:24:59,559 --> 00:25:01,039
I acted on my own
So I went ahead and

547
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:02,440
and gave them two million.

548
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:04,039
They've put their signatures

549
00:25:04,359 --> 00:25:05,279
and fingerprints on it.

550
00:25:05,480 --> 00:25:06,359
I have the evidence.

551
00:25:06,599 --> 00:25:08,119
There was a total of 60 million.

552
00:25:08,599 --> 00:25:10,160
I gave them two million,

553
00:25:10,279 --> 00:25:12,119
so there was 58 million left.

554
00:25:12,400 --> 00:25:13,759
However, this 58 million

555
00:25:13,920 --> 00:25:15,200
has all been scammed away

556
00:25:15,279 --> 00:25:16,160
by Chen Zinuo's mother.

557
00:25:16,359 --> 00:25:17,559
Jiang Juan and Zhan Chun,

558
00:25:17,680 --> 00:25:18,640
who kidnapped Wenwen

559
00:25:18,759 --> 00:25:20,240
and my mother-in-law,

560
00:25:20,319 --> 00:25:21,119
were after

561
00:25:21,119 --> 00:25:22,759
Hu Deshuai's 30 million

562
00:25:22,799 --> 00:25:24,599
in the wall.

563
00:25:24,759 --> 00:25:25,519
They didn't know

564
00:25:25,599 --> 00:25:26,599
there was 60 million here.

565
00:25:26,880 --> 00:25:27,440
I don't know

566
00:25:27,680 --> 00:25:28,559
if I've made myself clear.

567
00:25:29,960 --> 00:25:30,640
It's clear.

568
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:33,680
I remember you being

569
00:25:33,720 --> 00:25:34,599
a pretty timid guy.

570
00:25:35,039 --> 00:25:35,759
Something this big,

571
00:25:35,759 --> 00:25:36,519
and you held on that long?

572
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:37,559
Pretty impressive.

573
00:25:37,960 --> 00:25:39,160
Did it never cross your mind

574
00:25:39,240 --> 00:25:40,480
that if that 60 million was clean,

575
00:25:40,559 --> 00:25:41,480
why would someone wall it up

576
00:25:41,519 --> 00:25:42,160
or bury it underground?

577
00:25:42,680 --> 00:25:43,519
Now 60 million

578
00:25:43,599 --> 00:25:44,640
down to 58.

579
00:25:44,759 --> 00:25:45,519
That's definitely

580
00:25:45,519 --> 00:25:46,319
illegal possession.

581
00:25:46,519 --> 00:25:47,240
What was on your mind?

582
00:25:48,240 --> 00:25:49,359
Why didn't you turn yourself in?

583
00:25:49,559 --> 00:25:51,119
I thought about it and I even tried.

584
00:25:51,240 --> 00:25:52,400
Yitong went with me.

585
00:25:52,440 --> 00:25:53,480
She asked me to turn myself in.

586
00:25:53,519 --> 00:25:54,480
We went to see you.

587
00:25:54,559 --> 00:25:55,440
Do you remember it?

588
00:25:55,480 --> 00:25:57,839
But then I ran away.

589
00:25:58,759 --> 00:25:59,480
Why did you run away?

590
00:25:59,920 --> 00:26:01,079
Well, on that day, we got

591
00:26:01,079 --> 00:26:01,920
everything ready.

592
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:02,920
I wrote a letter about everything

593
00:26:02,960 --> 00:26:03,799
to my family.

594
00:26:03,799 --> 00:26:04,599
I had it all laid out.

